+Refactor the dashboard layout (likely in a file like dashboard/page.tsx, admin/MachinesOverview.tsx or similar component showing cards for machines/status/MQTT info) to achieve a clean, consistent, Linear.app-inspired design. Follow these exact changes:
+
+1. Make inner padding of the **first three cards** (probably the overview/summary cards at the top) **exactly the same** as the padding used in the MQTT status cards below them.
+   - Use the same Tailwind padding classes (e.g. p-6 or px-6 py-5) that are already applied to the MQTT cards — copy the value directly.
+
+2. Apply consistent outer spacing around **all cards and all buttons**:
+   - Add **margin: 15px** (Tailwind: m-4 ≈ 16px or mx-4 my-3.5 for closer to 14-15px) around every card container.
+   - If cards are in a grid or flex layout, ensure gap-4 or gap-6 is used between them, then add outer margin if needed so the whole group has breathing room from edges.
+
+3. Improve all buttons (primary, secondary, status indicators, actions like "Unlock", "Provision", etc.):
+   - Increase overall button size slightly: use px-5 py-2.5 or px-6 py-3 instead of default px-4 py-2.
+   - Add comfortable inner padding — aim for a more "clickable" feel without being huge.
+   - Keep rounded-md or rounded-lg for Linear-style softness.
+   - If buttons lack vertical padding feel, explicitly set py-2.5 or py-3.
+
+4. Style the 'connected' status field (likely a badge, pill, text or Card description showing connection state like WiFi/LTE):
+   - When the status is "connected" (or true/online), make text or background **green**.
+   - Use shadcn Badge variant="outline" or "secondary" with text-green-600 dark:text-green-400, or bg-green-100 text-green-800 dark:bg-green-950 dark:text-green-300 for a clean Linear-like accent.
+   - For disconnected/offline use red/gray accordingly if not already done.
