# 2026-02-28 15:34:06.584284
+Implement full runtime WiFi provisioning in waterfront-esp32 using ESP-IDF wifi_provisioning component.
+
+- Preferred: BLE transport (wifi_prov_scheme_ble) – secure pairing, works with nRF Connect / LightBlue.
+- Fallback: SoftAP + captive portal (wifi_prov_scheme_softap) with random WPA2 password shown on LED.
+- Trigger: 
+  1. First boot (if !wifi_prov_mgr_is_provisioned())
+  2. Long-press GPIO button (debounced)
+  3. Future MQTT command /kayak/{machineId}/provision/start (admin only)
+- Store SSID/password in NVS namespace "wifi"
+- After success: stop provisioning, restart WiFi STA, reconnect MQTT, publish {"wifiState":"connected","ssid":"...","ip":"..."}
+- Keep existing MQTT client alive.
+- Add to main.cpp + new files: provisioning.cpp / provisioning.h
+- Update platformio.ini with required components.
+- Include full beginner comments + test steps (nRF Connect flow).

# 2026-02-28 15:34:09.985715
+all

# 2026-02-28 15:38:35.677258
+Add LTE cellular fallback to waterfront-esp32 (TinyGSM + UART2).
+
+- Hardware: SIM7600/SIM7000 on UART2 (GPIO16/17), PWRKEY on GPIOx (MOSFET control).
+- State machine: Try WiFi 30s → if fail, power-up modem → LTE-M/NB-IoT → MQTT over TinyGSM TCP.
+- Prefer WiFi when available (power down modem).
+- Telemetry in /kayak/{machineId}/status: {"connType":"WiFi|LTE","rssi":-78,"dataKB":124}
+- Power optimisation: deep sleep modem when idle.
+- Test command: simulate WiFi fail → confirm unlock still arrives via LTE.
+- Update platformio.ini lib_deps.

