+Continue Waterfront booking + ESP32 MQTT control system.
+
+We now need FULL real-time slot booking synchronization + physical gate control using RETAINED MQTT topics.
+
+Required architecture (implement exactly):
+
+1. MQTT topic structure (all QoS 1, retained=true on status topics):
+   - waterfront/slots/{slotId}/status          ← retained JSON status (published by backend on every booking change)
+   - waterfront/slots/{slotId}/command         ← commands from backend (open_gate, close_gate, etc.)
+   - waterfront/slots/{slotId}/ack             ← ESP32 publishes confirmation back (retained=false)
+
+2. JSON payload schema for /status (retained):
+   {
+     "slotId": 3,
+     "booked": true,
+     "bookingId": "BKG-20260228-001",
+     "startTime": "2026-03-01T10:00:00Z",
+     "endTime": "2026-03-01T12:00:00Z",
+     "customerName": "Marco Rossi",
+     "gateState": "locked"
+   }
+
+3. ESP32 side (main.ino + mqtt_handler.cpp):
+   - Subscribe to waterfront/slots/+/status and waterfront/slots/+/command
+   - On status message: parse JSON → if booked==true and gateState=="locked" → call openGateServo(slotId), update 7-segment/LED matrix, publish ack
+   - On command message: direct servo/relay action
+   - Use ArduinoJson 7.x, PubSubClient (or AsyncMqttClient if already in project)
+   - Reconnect logic with last-will on disconnect
+   - Add debug Serial prints with millis()
+
+4. Backend side (booking_bridge.py or Node.js service):
+   - On new/updated/cancelled booking in DB → publish retained status to waterfront/slots/{slotId}/status
+   - Use paho-mqtt (Python) or mqtt.js with {retain: true}
+
+5. Add new files if missing:
+   - mqtt_topics.h (central topic definitions)
+   - gate_control.cpp + gate_control.h (servo + limit switch logic)
+
