# 2026-02-28 21:22:26.108253
+Add production-grade stability safeguards to waterfront-esp32 firmware:
+
+1. In main.cpp / app_main():
+   - Include <esp_task_wdt.h>
+   - Call esp_task_wdt_init(15, true);  // 15s timeout, panic on timeout
+   - esp_task_wdt_add(NULL);  // Subscribe current task (main)
+
+2. Create a new file src/error_handler.cpp / .h:
+   - void fatal_error(const char* msg, esp_err_t code = ESP_FAIL);
+     → ESP_LOGE("FATAL", "%s: %s (0x%x)", msg, esp_err_to_name(code), code);
+     → esp_restart(); after 5s delay
+
+3. In key init functions (wifi_manager_init, mqtt_client_init, lte_manager_init, gate_control_init):
+   - Wrap with if (ret != ESP_OK) fatal_error("Init failed", ret);
+
+4. In mqtt_callback and sensor_monitor_task:
+   - Add periodic esp_task_wdt_reset(); every loop iteration
+
+Show clean diffs for main.cpp, new error_handler files, and one example usage (e.g. mqtt_client_init).

