# 2026-02-28 21:31:49.810460
+Add runtime configuration via LittleFS JSON + MQTT remote update for waterfront-esp32:
+
+Goals:
+- Replace hard-coded values in config.h with runtime loading
+- Support admin-driven changes (e.g., add compartment, change MQTT broker)
+
+Steps:
+1. Add #include <LittleFS.h> and LittleFS.begin() in main.cpp / app_main() early
+2. Create config.json skeleton in data/ folder (or default in code):
+   {
+     "mqtt": {
+       "broker": "192.168.178.50",
+       "port": 1883,
+       "username": "",
+       "password": ""
+     },
+     "location": {
+       "slug": "bremen-harbor",
+       "code": "harbor-01"
+     },
+     "compartments": [
+       {"number":1, "servoPin":12, "limitOpenPin":13, "limitClosePin":14},
+       {"number":2, "servoPin":15, ...}
+     ],
+     "maxCompartments": 8
+   }
+3. In main.cpp: Load JSON → parse with ArduinoJson → populate globals/structs (e.g., vector<CompartmentConfig> compartments)
+4. In compartment_manager.cpp: Use loaded pins instead of hard-coded
+5. In mqtt_handler.cpp: Add subscription to /waterfront/{location}/{locationCode}/config/update
+   - On message: parse new JSON → LittleFS.write → ESP.restart() or reload in-place
+6. Fallback: If LittleFS fails / no file → use config.h defaults + log warning
+
+Show diffs for:
+- main.cpp (LittleFS init + load)
+- compartment_manager.cpp (use loaded config)
+- new config_loader.cpp/h if needed
+- platformio.ini (add LittleFS upload via extra_scripts or data folder)
+
+Keep backward compatible where possible.

