# 2026-02-28 21:40:41.094794
+Ensure ALL configuration is done ONLY in ONE central place: a runtime-loaded config.json via LittleFS. No more scattered #defines in config.h or hard-codes elsewhere. This makes the system easy to configure, debug, and scale for Bremen waterfront locations without re-flashing.
+Required:
+
+Config must include: MQTT (broker, port, user/pass), WiFi/LTE (APN, SIM PIN, RSSI thresholds), location (slug, code), compartments (array with number, servoPin, limitOpenPin, limitClosePin, sensorPin), maxCompartments, debugMode (true/false for verbose logs), gracePeriodSec (for overdue), etc. – pull from all current hard-codes in the codebase.
+Fallback: If config.json missing or corrupt, load defaults from a static struct in code + log warning + create default file.
+Runtime update: Subscribe to /waterfront/{location}/{locationCode}/config/update in mqtt_handler.cpp – on valid JSON, write to LittleFS + optional restart.
+Security: Validate JSON schema on load/update (e.g., check types, bounds for pins 0-39).
+
+Implementation steps:
+
+Add LittleFS to platformio.ini (lib_deps or build_flags if needed) + data/ folder with default config.json.
+Create new src/config_loader.cpp / .h:
+struct Config { /* all fields */ };
+Config globalConfig;
+bool loadConfig() { LittleFS.begin(); File f = LittleFS.open("/config.json", "r"); ArduinoJson parse; populate globalConfig; handle errors. }
+bool updateConfig(const char* json) { validate + write to /config.json + reload. }
+
+In main.cpp: Call loadConfig() early after nvs_flash_init(); fail to error_handler if critical.
+Update ALL files to use globalConfig fields:
+mqtt_client.cpp: globalConfig.mqtt.broker instead of MQTT_SERVER
+gate_control.cpp: Loop over globalConfig.compartments for pin setup
+lte_manager.cpp: globalConfig.lte.apn
+compartment_manager.cpp: Load from globalConfig.compartments
+etc. – search codebase for all #defines/hard-codes and replace.
+
+Deprecate config.h: Move any remaining to comments or delete.
+Add admin note in docs/TSD.md: "All config in /config.json – edit via MQTT or upload via PlatformIO data."
+
+Show diffs step-by-step: First config_loader.cpp/h + main.cpp, then one example (mqtt_client.cpp), then batch for others.
+Start with adding files, then edits. Commit as "feat: centralize all config in LittleFS JSON with runtime update".

