# 2026-02-28 21:47:15.904231
+Centralize ALL configuration in ONE place for waterfront-esp32 firmware.
+
+Goal: Eliminate every #define and hard-coded value from config.h and other files. Move everything into a single runtime-loaded /config.json on LittleFS. This makes the system fully configurable without re-flashing — critical for deploying to different Bremen waterfront locations.
+
+Requirements:
+- config.json must contain EVERY configurable item currently hard-coded anywhere:
+  - MQTT: broker (IP/domain), port, username, password, client_id prefix
+  - Location: slug ("bremen"), code ("harbor-01")
+  - WiFi provisioning defaults (fallback SSID/pass if needed)
+  - LTE: APN, SIM PIN (if locked), RSSI failover threshold, data usage alert limit
+  - Compartments: array of objects [{number:1, servoPin:12, limitOpenPin:13, limitClosePin:14, ultrasonicTriggerPin:15, ultrasonicEchoPin:16, weightSensorPin:17}, ...]
+  - System: maxCompartments (fallback), debugMode (bool), gracePeriodSec (for overdue), batteryLowThresholdPercent, solarVoltageMin
+  - Other: offline PIN list TTL, deposit hold amount fallback, etc.
+
+Implementation:
+1. Add LittleFS support:
+   - platformio.ini: ensure lib_deps includes filesystem if needed; add data/ folder with default config.json
+   - main.cpp: LittleFS.begin() right after nvs_flash_init(); if fail → fatal_error
+
+2. Create src/config_loader.cpp / config_loader.h:
+   - struct GlobalConfig { /* nested structs for mqtt, location, vector<CompartmentPinConfig> compartments, etc. */ };
+   - extern GlobalConfig g_config;
+   - bool loadConfig();               // parse /config.json → populate g_config; fallback to defaults if missing/corrupt
+   - bool saveConfig();               // serialize g_config back to /config.json
+   - bool updateConfigFromJson(const char* jsonPayload); // validate + save + reload globals
+
+3. In main.cpp: Call loadConfig() early → if critical fields missing → log + use minimal safe defaults
+
+4. Replace ALL usages:
+   - mqtt_client.cpp: g_config.mqtt.broker instead of MQTT_SERVER
+   - mqtt_handler.cpp: build topics using g_config.location.slug, g_config.location.code
+   - gate_control.cpp / compartment_manager.cpp: loop over g_config.compartments for pinMode/attachServo
+   - lte_manager.cpp: g_config.lte.apn
+   - Any other file with hard-codes: search & replace with g_config.*
+   - Deprecate config.h completely (keep as comment-only reference)
+
+5. MQTT remote config update:
+   - In mqtt_handler.cpp: subscribe to "waterfront/%s/%s/config/update" (using g_config location)
+   - On message: call updateConfigFromJson(payload); log success; optional ESP.restart() after 5s
+
+6. Default fallback struct in code (hard-coded minimal safe values)
+7. Add schema validation on load/update (ArduinoJson: check required keys, pin range 0-39, etc.)
+8. Update docs/ESP32 Pinout Plan and Diagram.md: "Pins now loaded from /config.json – edit via MQTT or PlatformIO data upload"
+
+Show diffs in this order:
+- platformio.ini + data/config.json (default)
+- new config_loader.cpp / .h
+- main.cpp (LittleFS + load)
+- mqtt_handler.cpp (remote update subscription)
+- one example handler (e.g. compartment_manager.cpp using g_config)
+- batch replace summary for remaining files
+
+Commit message: "feat: centralize all configuration in LittleFS /config.json with runtime MQTT update"
+
+Start now — add files first, then edits./clear

