# 2026-02-28 22:21:42.670119
+Add ESP32 watchdog and global error handling for production stability in waterfront-esp32.
+
+1. In src/main.cpp / app_main():
+   - #include <esp_task_wdt.h>
+   - esp_task_wdt_init(15, true);  // 15s timeout, panic/restart on timeout
+   - esp_task_wdt_add(NULL);       // Subscribe main task
+
+2. Create new src/error_handler.cpp / error_handler.h:
+   - void fatal_error(const char* msg, esp_err_t code = ESP_FAIL);
+     → ESP_LOGE("FATAL", "%s: %s (0x%x)", msg, esp_err_to_name(code), code);
+     → delay(5000); esp_restart();
+
+3. In init functions (wifi_manager_init, mqtt_client_init, lte_manager_init, gate_control_init, compartment_manager_init):
+   - If return != ESP_OK → fatal_error("Init failed", ret);
+
+4. In long-running tasks (mqtt_loop_task, sensor_monitor_task): call esp_task_wdt_reset() every ~1s.
+
+Show diffs: main.cpp, new error_handler files, and one example usage (e.g. mqtt_client_init).
+Commit as "feat: add watchdog and global fatal_error handler"

