+Create a comprehensive README.md inside the waterfront-esp32 folder.
+
+Content should include:
+
+1. Project overview (brief: ESP32 firmware for Waterfront unmanned compartment control via MQTT)
+
+2. Hardware requirements (ESP32-S3, SIM7600 LTE, servo, ultrasonic, limit switches, pins loaded from config.json)
+
+3. Quick start:
+   - pio run -t upload
+   - pio run -t uploadfs  (for initial /config.json)
+   - pio device monitor -b 115200
+
+4. Configuration:
+   - All settings in data/config.json (MQTT broker, location, compartment pins, debugMode, etc.)
+   - Remote update via MQTT topic waterfront/{location}/{locationCode}/config/update
+   - Example config.json snippet
+
+5. Testing:
+   - Unit tests: pio test -e unit_test
+   - Manual MQTT test: mosquitto_pub commands for status/command/config
+
+6. Debug tips:
+   - Serial @ 115200
+   - ESP_LOG levels (set debugMode: true)
+   - Common issues: wrong broker → check logs, pin conflicts → use config
+
+7. Development notes:
+   - Non-blocking everywhere (millis + FreeRTOS)
+   - Dynamic compartments loaded from config
+   - Security TODO: TLS + auth
+
+8. Folder structure overview (src/, test/, data/)
+
+Keep it clean, markdown-formatted, with code blocks for examples.
+
